The paper proposes a novel Generative Adversarial Network (GAN) framework for Multi-View Network Embedding, which is a machine learning technique for representing multi-view networks in low-dimensional space. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper deals with network representation learning. Additionally, the paper also discusses node classification, link prediction, and visualization tasks, which are related to cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
